SIMPLE: solve
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Solve
<hw>Solve</hw> <pr>(s⟦ocr⟧lv)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Solved</conjf> <pr>(s⟦ocr⟧lvd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Solving</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>solvere</ets>, <ets>solutum</ets>; from a prefix <ets>so-</ets>
expressing separation (cf. <er>Sober</er>) + <ets>luere</ets> to loosen;
cf. OF. <ets>soldre</ets>, <ets>soudre</ets>. See <er>Loose</er>, and
cf. <er>Absolve</er>.]</ety> <def>To explain; to resolve; to unfold; to
clear up (what is obscure or difficult to be understood); to work out to
a result or conclusion; <as>as, to <ex>solve</ex> a doubt; to
<ex>solve</ex> difficulties; to <ex>solve</ex> a problem</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>True piety would effectually <qex>solve</qex> such scruples.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God shall <qex>solve</qex> the dark decrees of fate.</q>
<rj><qau>Tickell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To explain; resolve; unfold; clear up.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Solve</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Solve
<hw>Solve</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A solution; an explanation.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Solvency</ent>⟦br⟧
